===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Happening or [[occur]]ring during [[daylight]], or primarily [[active]] during that time.
#: ''Most birds are '''diurnal'''.''
#* '''1972''', Laurence Monroe Klauber, [https://books.google.com/books?id=ijblNZQrk_wC&pg=PA447&dq=%22more+diurnal%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjRmeiD3OTOAhVFxGMKHRvzBpgQ6AEIRDAH#v=onepage&q=%22more%20diurnal%22&f=false Rattlesnakes: Their Habits, Life Histories, and Influence on Mankind, Volume 1]
#*: However, in general, lizards are more '''diurnal''' than rattlers, which may be one of the reasons why young rattlers are more '''diurnal''' than adults.
#* Shakespeare
#*: Ere twice the horses of the sun shall bring / Their fiery torcher his '''diurnal''' ring.
# {{lb|en|botany}} Said of a flower [[open]], or releasing its [[perfume]] during daylight hours, but not at night.
# Having a daily [[cycle]] that is completed every 24 hours, usually referring to [[tasks]], [[processes]], [[tides]], or [[sunrise]] to [[sunset]]; [[circadian]].
# {{lb|en|uncommon}} Done [[once]] every day; [[daily]], [[quotidian]].
# {{lb|en|archaic}} [[publish|Published]] daily.

